5:
I didn't expect you to call for me. Are
your injuries all healed up now?
9:
Yes. I've become well acquainted
with how depressing excessive sleep
can be.
16:
What are you thinking of doing if I
told you?
20:
...Back then, I really heard their
voices for the first time.
22:
They were suffering. Grieving deeply.
I can't ignore their cries... nor do I
wish to.
25:
But I also can't think of a good idea.
No matter what, I can only seem to
think in extremes.
29:
That's why I'd like to borrow some
ideas from you. Just what should I
do with myself?
33:
...Oho! Somebody's gotten a lot
more honest with their feelings, huh?
42:
I've got just the thing to share with
you, Magnos.
48:
Catfolk and dogfolk? What are they
doing here?
51:
They're mercenaries. Not regular
soldiers, as you can see.
54:
Among them are those who couldn't
return to soldier life, those who
couldn't become a soldier in the first
place, and people of all other sorts.
56:
But this is all they can do. The only
life for them is on the battlefield, and
that's why they're here.
64:
At the very least, I want to ensure
they don't lose their purpose. They're
mercenaries, and they believe this is
all they have.
66:
They'll be guarding the joint city
shared by the dogfolk and catfolk.
After that... They're discussing using
their contacts to go somewhere far
away.
76:
Still, not all of them could adapt to
this life so easily.
79:
Those who got their hands dirty, in
particular...
83:
...Many of them would be the dogfolk
soldiers sent to mop things up...
91:
W-we've got trouble! There's a riot in
the city!
99:
Most of the troublemakers have
been subdued. The only ones left
are the ones from Magnos' former
group—
107:
Lay down your arms and come
quietly, and your lives will be spared!
Go no furth—
110: Shut up! Our war's not over just yet!
111:
If the world refuses to recognize us,
then we'll keep on fighting until we
die!
117: Please... I want to help them.
121:
I believe you. But are you sure you
want to do this?
132:
I am completely unarmed. I'm
concealing nothing, and you may
inspect me if you wish.
136:
Not a dagger to be found...
Well? The hell do you want?
143:
...Are you nuts? What do you think
you can do?
145:
We're not going to fall for your
promises a second time! The world
won't change... So we'll leave this
world with a scar that won't fade...
148:
...Do you pride yourselves on holding
innocent civilians hostage and
demanding a sacrifice?
152:
Are you certain this is how you'll
obtain what you always wished for?
155:
You made me burn that village to
the ground and hurt the innocent!
You can't put a stop to things now!
157:
It's your fault! Everything's your fault!
If it weren't for you, none of us would
be like this!
163:
I pretended not to hear you. I should
have understood your pain, your
cries...
166:
I didn't want to hurt you, but I didn't
want to be hurt either.
169:
...I couldn't acknowledge that, and
so I covered it all up in foolish ideals.
176:
Let's start over again. This time, we'll
handle things differently.
179:
Handle things differently? It's way
too late for that—
183:
It's never too late! For those who
seek neither recompense nor
retribution for their sins, but only the
strength for tomorrow...
185: There are those who will listen to us!
193:
Let us go to a place where we can
be accepted!
196:
...Your word by itself isn't good
enough.
198:
...Let me see it with my own eyes,
and then I'll judge what you've told
us.
207:
I see. You've managed to find
another way for them, too?
211:
...I wonder. Perhaps I merely want to
believe I've succeeded.
213:
There was a lot of enthusiasm back
there. I may very well still be wrong,
and that worries me...
216:
But you both chose to believe in me,
and so did they. I don't want to let
you down.
219: So I'll do everything I can.
228:
Whitetail. I take back what I said
earlier.
231:
I, too, decided to fight.
...That is all.
240:
He's really no good at being upfront
with his feelings...
